cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "The Sigil Benchmark: Production Readiness Score (PRS)"
abstract: >-
  An open methodology and reference implementation for measuring the
  production readiness of AI-generated software. PRS evaluates code outputs
  from AI coding tools across five dimensions — Security, Production
  Readiness Ops, Scalability, Compliance, and Cost Efficiency — using static
  analysis, dynamic probing, and bootstrapped statistical methods. PRS fills
  the gap left by capability-focused benchmarks (HELM, SWE-bench, HumanEval)
  by measuring whether AI-generated output is actually safe to ship.
message: >-
  If you use the Sigil Benchmark in research or evaluation, please cite as
  below.
